50|$|The United States {{has been}} Japan's largest {{economic}} partner, taking 31.5 {{percent of its}} exports, supplying 22.3 percent of its imports, and accounting for 45.9 percent of its <b>direct</b> <b>investment</b> <b>abroad</b> in 1990. As of 2013, the United States takes up 18% of Japanese exports, and supplies 8.5% of its imports (the slack having been picked up by China, which now provides 22%).|$|E
