50|$|According to Statistics Canada, the EU is {{also the}} second largest source of foreign direct {{investment}} (FDI) in Canada, with the stock of FDI amounting to $133.1 billion {{at the end of}} 2008. In 2008, the stock of Canada's direct investment in the EU totalled $136.6 billion, and the EU is the destination of 21.4% of Canadian <b>direct</b> <b>investment</b> <b>abroad.</b> According to Eurostat, the EU identified Canada as its third largest destination and its fourth largest source of FDI in 2007.|$|E
